Combined Oxford and Cambridge Universities tour of Jamaica 1938

All matches at Sabina Park, Kingston

 1- 8 All-Jamaica               1-2  Oxford and Cambridge
 9- 8 Kingston Club             1-6  Oxford and Cambridge
15- 8 St George's/Melbourne XI  0-2  Oxford and Cambridge
17- 8 Sherwood Foresters        2-0  Oxford and Cambridge
19- 8 All-Jamaica               2-1  Oxford and Cambridge
25- 8 Kingston Club             2-3  Oxford and Cambridge
27- 8 Sherwood Foresters        0-1  Oxford and Cambridge
29- 8 All-Jamaica               0-1  Oxford and Cambridge

The tour also involved several cricket matches, only two of which were first-class (both vs All-Jamaica).
10-13 August, draw.
20-24 August, Jamaica won by an innings and 74 runs.

Squad (footballers and cricketers): 

